<p style="text-align:justify;">they are so few in number, that they dare not go the lengths many of them would seemingly wish.  However with all their bad qualities, I must do them the justice to say that they do not appear to be addicted to theft.  They do not appear to have any principal Head or Chief; and are constantly talking of and even making prepations for going to war, but their ardour seems to abate with the severity of the winter.  They are so remarkably fond of liquor, that were their Country rich in Beaver, great profits might be made by them; but unfortunately it is quite the reverse: their lands are so poor and drained of Beaver &amp;c. that they can hardly pay for their absolute necessaries in good peltries.  Superstition appears to be their only religion &#8211; an instance of this happened last winter: in course of conversation, one of my Indians told me, that he had seen two Bears in their Dens, in the month of February &#8211; on my asking him, why</p>

